column5: Morning Brian. Have a great day! I was flippin' through some older tunes this morning and found this one. The boys are my age now! Of course, they were back then as well.  It's nice to see those guys get together again after that many years.  A question to you guts though...I was wondering if Opry North (I think it was sponsored by CFGM in the mid 70's) still exists.  Was written as a work song but the Fendermen did it as a feel good tune. Worth a listen just to see the joy in their faces now.  <object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="  Turn your sound up and have a great day!
Oh boy Roy, is Sue mad now! I did what you said, "turned up the sound"...... I told her "Roy" said to but she ain't happy  Loved it BTW!
LOL Roy had that one bookmarked, along with this.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Okd0CFLyvlM
GOOD MORNING!  Now pass around the jug
A good mornin' to all y'all!!!  Good tune Roy!  here's another:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pl0jYYK5AAQ  TGIF!
A simpler time Roy, didn`t take much to make people happy.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=maRHBwtY1Qo...feature=related

Watta way to start the day !!!  Some great tunes and an invite to go fishin' from Big Cliff...
Anyone want to join Beans and I on Lake X on Monday? Sure looks like a perfect day for it, light winds, sun, +2.
